sequenceDiagram
    actor User as Guest / Admin
    participant fe@{ "type": "boundary" } as Frontend
    participant API@{ "type": "control" } as API
    participant ms@{ "type": "control" } as Meilisearch

    Note over User,ms: Public room search with filters

    User->>+fe: Enter query "beach" + filters (city, price, guests)
    fe->>+API: GET /room/search?q=beach&city=...&minPrice=...&maxPrice=...&maxGuests=...
    API->>API: Read req.user (optional — public route)
    API->>API: isAdmin = req.user?.role === 'ADMIN'

    API->>API: Build filter object<br/>{ city?, minPrice?, maxPrice?, maxGuests?,<br/> + (status='APPROVED' unless admin) }

    API->>+ms: searchRooms(q, filters)
    ms->>ms: Compose filter string:<br/>city = "..." AND pricePerNight >= ...<br/>AND pricePerNight <= ... AND maxGuests >= ...<br/>AND status = "APPROVED"
    ms->>ms: index('rooms').search(q, { filter, sort:[createdAt:desc] })

    alt Meilisearch error
        ms-->>API: Error (logged)
        API-->>fe: 500 or empty
        fe-->>User: Show "Search unavailable"
    else Search ok
        ms-->>-API: { hits: [...rooms] }
        API-->>-fe: 200 { data: hits }
        fe-->>-User: Render room cards
    end

    Note over User,ms: Admins see PENDING/REJECTED rooms in search too —<br/>guests only see APPROVED.
